This is an Americanized spelling and the name that descended down through my family.

This is the original Danish spelling. This is the spelling on the 1900 US Census.  At the time of his birth, patronymics was still in force so his surname would have been Rasmussen.  He used the name Dinesen in the United States.  He is very specific in his journal that the name was and should remain spelled "Dinesen".  His children did not  maintain the name or spelling, consequently there are several variations of the name being used today.
